{"id":"2007.15127","submitter":"Christophe Ndjatchi","authors":"J. Lea\\~nos, Christophe Ndjatchi and L. M. R\\'ios-Castro","title":"On the connectivity of the disjointness graph of segments of point sets\n  in general position in the plane","comments":"16 pages, 5 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  Let $P$ be a set of $n\\geq 3$ points in general position in the plane. The\nedge disjointness graph $D(P)$ of $P$ is the graph whose vertices are all the\nclosed straight line segments with endpoints in $P$, two of which are adjacent\nin $D(P)$ if and only if they are disjoint. We show that the connectivity of\n$D(P)$ is at least\n$\\binom{\\lfloor\\frac{n-2}{2}\\rfloor}{2}+\\binom{\\lceil\\frac{n-2}{2}\\rceil}{2}$,\nand that this bound is tight for each $n\\geq 3$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 29 Jul 2020 21:56:40 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 24 Aug 2021 16:08:50 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 10 Dec 2021 02:13:50 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 5 Apr 2022 01:45:06 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Mon, 2 May 2022 17:20:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-03"}
